WEBVTT

00:09.676 --> 00:13.471
["It's A Good Day" by Peggy Lee playing]

00:17.058 --> 00:18.935
<i>♪ Yes, it's a good day  ♪</i>

00:19.269 --> 00:20.645
<i>♪ For singin' a song ♪</i>

00:20.729 --> 00:22.731
<i>♪ And it's a good day ♪</i>

00:23.106 --> 00:24.274
<i>♪ For movin' along ♪</i>

00:24.566 --> 00:26.484
<i>♪ Yes, it's a good day ♪</i>

00:26.568 --> 00:28.945
<i>♪ How could anything be wrong? ♪</i>

00:29.029 --> 00:31.823
<i>♪ A good day from morning till night ♪</i>

00:32.532 --> 00:34.325
<i>♪ And it's a good day ♪</i>

00:34.743 --> 00:36.161
<i>♪ For shinin' your shoes ♪</i>

00:36.244 --> 00:38.371
<i>♪ And it's a good day ♪</i>

00:38.663 --> 00:40.623
<i>♪ For losin' the blues ♪</i>

00:40.915 --> 00:44.461
<i>♪ Everything to gain and nothing to lose ♪</i>

00:44.586 --> 00:47.380
<i>♪ A good day from morning till night ♪</i>

00:48.548 --> 00:49.924
<i>♪ I said to the sun ♪</i>

00:50.383 --> 00:52.594
<i>♪ Good morning, sun ♪</i>

00:52.844 --> 00:55.305
<i>♪ Rise and shine today ♪</i>

00:55.597 --> 00:57.599
<i>♪ So take a deep breath ♪</i>

00:57.932 --> 00:59.768
<i>♪ And throw away the pills ♪</i>

00:59.851 --> 01:03.063
<i>♪ 'Cause it's a good day</i>
<i>From morning till night ♪</i>

01:03.855 --> 01:05.815
[flames crackle]

01:08.860 --> 01:11.404
-[bell tolls]
-[choral singing]

01:33.468 --> 01:34.636
[Jen] You see what happens?

01:35.011 --> 01:36.805
You live with your grandmother
for three days,

01:36.888 --> 01:38.556
and your brother becomes a Christian.

01:38.640 --> 01:40.934
[rabbi recites
"Mourner's Kaddish" in Hebrew]

01:53.738 --> 01:54.572
[all] Amen.

01:55.448 --> 01:56.282
Amen.

01:56.366 --> 01:57.408
[Christopher] <i>Where's Judy?</i>

01:57.742 --> 01:58.576
Um...

01:59.160 --> 02:00.328
Judy's not coming.

02:01.454 --> 02:03.706
She's... not gonna be
in our lives anymore.

02:03.790 --> 02:05.542
Isn't she, like, your best friend?

02:06.334 --> 02:07.418
What? No.

02:08.128 --> 02:09.295
No, not at all.

02:09.963 --> 02:11.047
Barely knew her.

02:13.758 --> 02:15.343
Then why did you let her live with us?

02:16.302 --> 02:20.056
You guys wanna have this chitchat later?
Henry's about to become a child of Christ.

02:20.306 --> 02:21.307
[Judy] <i>Excuse me, rabbi.</i>

02:21.766 --> 02:24.060
I just wanna say
it was such a nice service.

02:24.602 --> 02:25.979
I love that prayer.

02:26.604 --> 02:27.814
It was beautiful.

02:28.523 --> 02:29.357
What did it mean?

02:29.440 --> 02:32.360
That despite losing someone we love,
we still praise God.

02:33.111 --> 02:35.280
Even though God
took away the person we love?

02:35.363 --> 02:37.615
If we want God to forgive us,
we have to forgive Him.

02:38.741 --> 02:39.617
I like that.

02:40.160 --> 02:42.412
It's nice to think of Abe
up in Heaven with God.

02:43.413 --> 02:46.875
That is nice to think of, but...
there is no Heaven.

02:47.876 --> 02:49.961
-Really?
-No Hell either.

02:50.837 --> 02:51.713
Really?

02:52.714 --> 02:55.633
No matter how much bad someone's done
or how many people you've hurt?

02:56.134 --> 02:58.803
Well, in the Jewish faith,
if you've hurt someone,

02:58.887 --> 03:00.346
you've got to try to make amends.

03:00.930 --> 03:03.516
Find a way to compensate
for what you've done wrong.

03:04.976 --> 03:05.935
Thank you.

03:06.895 --> 03:07.729
Shalom.

03:08.396 --> 03:10.148
Henry Theodore Harding,

03:11.107 --> 03:13.318
we now wash away your original sin.

03:13.401 --> 03:14.944
What's original sin?

03:15.737 --> 03:18.865
Basically,
we're all born guilty and sinful.

03:19.324 --> 03:22.535
But then when we get baptized,
it's like we get a do-over.

03:23.077 --> 03:27.832
Then, all you have to do is ask for
forgiveness and you get a clean slate.

03:28.458 --> 03:29.584
Isn't that nice?

03:31.794 --> 03:33.755
[whispers] She's totally
fucking lying to you.

03:34.255 --> 03:36.925
[Wayne] Through baptism,
we are all one in Jesus Christ.

03:37.008 --> 03:39.302
-[Christopher squeals]
-[Wayne] I baptize you in the name...

03:39.385 --> 03:40.803
-of the Father and the son...
-Sorry.

03:40.887 --> 03:42.305
...and of the Holy Spirit.

03:54.025 --> 03:55.568
[Ana] Mrs. Harding. Hi.

03:55.693 --> 03:57.070
Judy Hale killed my husband.

03:58.404 --> 03:59.239
Yeah?

04:00.073 --> 04:02.492
Yeah? What do you mean, "yeah"?

04:03.243 --> 04:07.330
I mean, as of recently, I've been
made aware of her possible involvement.

04:07.705 --> 04:09.374
No, no. No, it is not possible.

04:09.457 --> 04:10.583
It is definite.

04:11.125 --> 04:12.418
She confessed it to me.

04:12.502 --> 04:13.336
Okay.

04:13.878 --> 04:14.712
I...

04:15.129 --> 04:17.048
I feel like you're being
cavalier about this.

04:17.131 --> 04:18.549
I'm not trying to be cavalier.

04:18.633 --> 04:21.135
-Well, then go arrest her.
-It doesn't work that way.

04:21.219 --> 04:22.720
There are much bigger factors involved.

04:22.804 --> 04:24.347
What factors? God!

04:24.430 --> 04:26.391
The way you talk
fucking annoys the shit out of me.

04:26.474 --> 04:28.434
I'm sorry. But I can't.

04:28.518 --> 04:29.894
It involves another investigation.

04:29.978 --> 04:32.480
And until that plays itself out,
my hands are tied with Ms. Hale.

04:32.563 --> 04:36.317
And even then, if she confesses,
it's not enough to warrant an arrest.

04:36.401 --> 04:40.738
She is a murderer and she is
walking around free as a fucking bird.

04:40.822 --> 04:42.198
You have to do something.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.159
Okay, I can get you a restraining order.
That'll take me about 24 hours.

04:46.786 --> 04:50.081
She killed my husband
and then she moved in with me.

04:50.999 --> 04:53.084
A restraining order isn't gonna do it.

04:54.168 --> 04:56.296
Thank you for fucking nothing again.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.840
Mrs. Harding, wait. Mrs. Harding.

04:59.465 --> 05:02.844
For now, try and take comfort
knowing that you have your answer.

05:02.927 --> 05:04.012
Isn't that what you wanted?

05:05.096 --> 05:08.016
You want me to take comfort
in the fact that we live in a world

05:08.099 --> 05:10.768
where everyone knows what the truth is
and there are no consequences?

05:11.352 --> 05:13.229
There will be consequences, I assure you.

05:13.313 --> 05:14.939
Oh, no. I assure you.

05:22.822 --> 05:24.741
Look at us working together again.

05:25.366 --> 05:26.784
[chuckles] Look at us.

05:27.577 --> 05:31.539
You know, I have to say, having Charlie
at my house has been a real godsend.

05:32.040 --> 05:33.416
It's like having Ted back.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.209
Well, yeah. It's just a phase.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.920
Charlie will come home
when he's done being mad at me.

05:38.004 --> 05:39.839
-Well, I'm glad to be able to help.
-Okay.

05:39.922 --> 05:42.258
Be someone you can turn to.
That's what family's for.

05:44.677 --> 05:45.720
You look tired.

05:46.137 --> 05:49.098
Lorna, I just sold two
of these units for you all cash.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.768
What is it gonna take for you
to just lay off?

05:52.185 --> 05:54.896
Well, you didn't sell anything.

05:54.979 --> 05:55.813
What?

05:56.147 --> 05:58.274
Steve Wood pulled his deposit
this morning.

05:58.733 --> 05:59.734
I thought you knew.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.070
-Why?
-I don't know. He's your client.

06:02.904 --> 06:03.946
Oh, shit.

06:04.364 --> 06:06.741
Well, don't dwell. Circulate the trays.

06:06.824 --> 06:10.203
And do one more Swiffer of the bathrooms.
I want that faux marble spotless.

06:10.286 --> 06:11.496
Yup. Of course.

06:15.708 --> 06:16.834
Hi. Would you like one?

06:16.918 --> 06:18.419
-No.
-Okay. Great.

06:25.885 --> 06:27.512
-May I offer you a pinwheel?
-No.

06:30.223 --> 06:32.809
Hi. Would either of you like
to try one of these?

06:32.892 --> 06:33.976
-No.
-Okay.

06:39.857 --> 06:40.733
Hi.

06:41.067 --> 06:42.777
Good afternoon. Would you like a pinwheel?

06:42.860 --> 06:44.070
-[man] No.
-Okay. Good.

06:46.030 --> 06:47.031
[sighs]

07:10.805 --> 07:11.889
-Hi.
-[Jen gasps]

07:12.140 --> 07:13.266
Get the fuck out of here!

07:13.349 --> 07:14.976
-Don't make a scene.
-Get the fuck out!

07:15.059 --> 07:17.520
-Let me help you.
-No, don't fucking help me.

07:17.603 --> 07:18.813
-Shh.
-You shh!

07:18.896 --> 07:19.730
Okay.

07:20.106 --> 07:21.399
-You look really nice.
-Shut up.

07:21.482 --> 07:23.443
-Okay.
-What the fuck are you doing here?

07:23.526 --> 07:25.111
How dare you fucking show up here?

07:25.611 --> 07:28.823
I'm working for Lorna
to keep a roof over my kids' heads,

07:28.906 --> 07:30.366
to keep my life together.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.993
A life that you destroyed.

07:32.076 --> 07:32.952
I know.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.954
That's why I'm turning myself in.

07:35.037 --> 07:37.665
I just wanted you to know I'm gonna
ask for the maximum sentence.

07:37.748 --> 07:40.251
It might be the chair
if that's something that they still do,

07:40.334 --> 07:42.462
but the worst punishment of all
is losing you.

07:46.007 --> 07:47.467
Well, I already turned you in.

07:49.218 --> 07:52.597
Yeah. Okay. That's... You should have.
That's right.

07:52.680 --> 07:53.931
-That's right.
-Good for you.

07:54.015 --> 07:55.141
-Shut up.
-Okay.

07:55.850 --> 07:59.687
It doesn't even fucking matter,
because your confession isn't enough.

08:00.313 --> 08:04.567
So you get to go walk free and fuck
with my head as much as you want to.

08:04.650 --> 08:06.027
I don't wanna fuck with your head.

08:06.110 --> 08:09.572
-Then what do you fucking want, Judy?
-I want to just make amends.

08:09.655 --> 08:11.532
I want you to be okay.

08:13.284 --> 08:14.869
You want me to be okay?

08:14.952 --> 08:15.870
Yeah.

08:17.371 --> 08:20.458
You hit my husband and left him to die.

08:21.250 --> 08:24.587
Then you stalk me, you move into my home,

08:25.046 --> 08:27.006
you get my children to trust you.

08:27.465 --> 08:29.509
You are a fucking sociopath.

08:29.759 --> 08:31.844
-I love you.
-I fucking hate you.

08:33.471 --> 08:34.472
Okay.

08:35.139 --> 08:36.766
Stay the fuck away from me.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.936
If there's anything that I can do...

08:40.019 --> 08:42.605
You know what you can do?
You can disappear off the fucking planet.

08:45.483 --> 08:46.609
Okay.

08:47.735 --> 08:50.321
I have Ted's gun in... in my purse.

08:51.906 --> 08:57.370
So, if I see you again
or you go anywhere near my family...

08:58.496 --> 09:01.249
I will shoot you in the fucking head.

09:01.791 --> 09:03.042
Do you understand me?

09:03.417 --> 09:05.586
Yeah... I do.

09:05.836 --> 09:08.089
Get the fuck out
and don't even come near me.

09:08.172 --> 09:09.966
Get the fuck out of here, Judy.

09:12.885 --> 09:14.178
Go. Now!

09:20.184 --> 09:21.352
[breathing shakily]

09:53.384 --> 09:55.678
Yes, Howard. I'm not a fucking idiot.
I know...

09:55.761 --> 09:57.763
Obviously somebody
fucking talked to the...

09:58.306 --> 09:59.599
I don't know who.

10:00.391 --> 10:03.686
Listen, I'm handling it. I just
gotta move some cash around at the bank.

10:03.769 --> 10:05.438
-[phone beeps]
-Hang on. Would you hang on?

10:07.148 --> 10:08.774
Fuck! I gotta call you back.

10:09.150 --> 10:10.776
-[phone beeps]
-[sighs]

10:11.694 --> 10:12.820
[cheerily] Stavros.

10:14.071 --> 10:15.489
Stavros... Hey.

10:15.906 --> 10:18.618
[speaking Greek]

10:19.785 --> 10:23.039
Yeah, I know you can speak English,
but my Greek is pretty good, right?

10:24.165 --> 10:24.999
Oh.

10:26.083 --> 10:28.753
[woman] <i>How much were you looking</i>
<i>to withdraw from the joint account?</i>

10:29.712 --> 10:30.963
All of it, please.

10:31.297 --> 10:32.715
In a cashier's check.

10:33.841 --> 10:35.635
So you wanna close out the account?

10:36.135 --> 10:37.011
That's right.

10:37.386 --> 10:39.639
Well, we're certainly sorry to see you go.

10:39.722 --> 10:42.308
May I ask why you decided
to leave Orange Coast Trust?

10:44.852 --> 10:45.811
I'm going away.

10:48.981 --> 10:50.816
-[door opens]
-[Jen] Hey, Karen.

10:51.025 --> 10:53.277
Sorry it took me so long
to get this back to you. I just...

10:53.361 --> 10:56.197
Anyway, whatever was in it was delicious.

10:56.572 --> 10:58.324
It was my take on Mexican lasagna.

10:58.532 --> 10:59.992
Mmm, right. Right.

11:00.076 --> 11:01.994
Well... thank you.

11:02.370 --> 11:03.704
There weren't too many raisins?

11:04.538 --> 11:05.665
Uh-uh.

11:05.915 --> 11:07.458
-No way.
-[Karen laughs]

11:08.084 --> 11:09.752
-All right. Well, thanks.
-Mm-hm.

11:14.131 --> 11:14.965
Um...

11:16.842 --> 11:17.885
Would you...

11:19.637 --> 11:23.140
Do you wanna... come by later,

11:23.557 --> 11:27.561
like, after the kids go to sleep
and have a glass of wine by the pool?

11:28.104 --> 11:29.605
You mean socialize?

11:31.440 --> 11:32.983
-Yeah.
-Okay.

11:33.067 --> 11:34.610
-Okay.
-Great.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.112
-So I'll see you there?
-Cool.

11:36.195 --> 11:37.405
-By the pool.
-Yeah.

11:37.488 --> 11:39.073
-Okay.
-Your pool...

11:39.156 --> 11:40.074
What?

11:40.241 --> 11:41.450
Your house?

11:42.576 --> 11:43.661
-Yeah.
-Yeah, okay.

11:44.036 --> 11:46.080
-Do you want me to bring anything?
-No. No.

11:46.163 --> 11:48.332
I could whip something up. I don't work.

11:48.416 --> 11:49.458
No, please don't.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.210
-Just don't do that.
-Okay.

11:51.585 --> 11:53.003
Thanks. See you later.

11:53.087 --> 11:54.255
-See you later.
-Bye.

11:58.008 --> 11:59.885
[teller] <i>Sorry,</i>
<i>that account has been closed.</i>

12:00.428 --> 12:01.846
-Sorry, what?
-Yes.

12:01.929 --> 12:04.265
The joint person on the account? Ms. Hale.

12:06.475 --> 12:07.601
She was here earlier.

12:08.519 --> 12:11.397
She was here earlier and she what?
She what?

12:11.981 --> 12:13.399
-She...
-She closed the account.

12:20.781 --> 12:21.615
Cool.

12:21.699 --> 12:23.075
Um... Thank you.

12:27.705 --> 12:29.707
[breathing heavily]

12:32.042 --> 12:33.627
[roars]

12:33.794 --> 12:35.546
Fucking Judy! I'm gonna fucking kill her!

12:36.046 --> 12:38.048
["Every Breath You Take" playing]

12:50.436 --> 12:53.272
[Christopher] Snap and kick.
Snap. Kick. Good. Okay.

12:53.355 --> 12:56.358
[children]  ♪ <i>Every breath you take ♪</i>

12:57.401 --> 12:59.820
<i>♪ Every move you make ♪</i>

12:59.904 --> 13:01.071
[Christopher] Henry, yes.

13:01.238 --> 13:05.367
<i>♪ Every bond you break</i>
<i>Every step you take</i> ♪

13:05.451 --> 13:06.410
<i>♪ He'll be watching... ♪</i>

13:06.494 --> 13:07.912
[Christopher] Owen, very good.

13:08.329 --> 13:09.872
Yep. Yep. Yep.

13:09.955 --> 13:13.918
<i>♪ Every single day</i> ♪

13:14.001 --> 13:17.004
<i>♪ Every word you say ♪</i>

13:18.088 --> 13:20.174
<i>♪ Every game you play ♪</i>

13:20.257 --> 13:22.176
<i>♪ Every night you stay ♪</i>

13:22.259 --> 13:24.345
<i>♪ He'll be watching you ♪</i>

13:26.472 --> 13:27.431
[Christopher] Keep going.

13:27.515 --> 13:30.559
<i>♪ Oh, can't you see</i> ♪

13:31.101 --> 13:32.311
[Christopher] Judy, hi.

13:32.895 --> 13:35.064
I'm sorry, this is a closed rehearsal.

13:35.648 --> 13:36.857
Oh, okay. I'm sorry.

13:36.941 --> 13:41.028
I have a little gift for Henry
in honor of his baptism and I thought...

13:42.363 --> 13:44.657
Well, maybe you could
give it to him for me.

13:44.740 --> 13:45.574
Sure.

13:45.908 --> 13:47.368
I'm his godfather, after all.

13:48.118 --> 13:49.954
He's very lucky to have you.

13:51.622 --> 13:52.540
Yeah.

13:53.499 --> 13:57.795
Hey, what happened with Jen?
Why did you move out?

13:59.296 --> 14:00.381
She didn't tell you?

14:00.464 --> 14:02.925
No, she won't talk about it.

14:03.008 --> 14:06.554
So I assume a violent outburst
is imminent?

14:10.140 --> 14:12.142
Just be kind to her, please.

14:12.476 --> 14:14.395
She really needs a friend right now.

14:15.229 --> 14:16.188
Okay.

14:17.022 --> 14:18.274
I do need you to go.

14:18.357 --> 14:19.775
The kids aren't audience-ready.

14:19.859 --> 14:26.532
<i>♪ I keep trying baby, baby</i>
<i>Please</i> ♪

14:30.578 --> 14:32.371
-Hop into bed, honey.
-Okay.

14:32.454 --> 14:35.040
I just have one last thing
I need to go over with you.

14:35.541 --> 14:37.626
-Okay.
-Okay. You see this over here?

14:37.960 --> 14:38.919
This white thing?

14:39.295 --> 14:40.379
-Yeah.
-That's a sensor.

14:40.462 --> 14:45.342
So if the bird that you think is
your daddy comes to the window,

14:45.843 --> 14:48.053
you can't talk to him
until I turn the alarm off.

14:48.137 --> 14:50.764
It's okay.
Judy got me a bird I can keep inside.

14:52.182 --> 14:54.643
-What?
-You wanna see? It's for my baptism.

14:55.311 --> 14:56.145
Um...

14:57.354 --> 14:58.856
When did you see Judy, Henry?

14:59.106 --> 15:02.693
She came to the Holy Harmonies practice,
but Christopher kicked her out.

15:03.110 --> 15:05.446
He doesn't like people seeing us
in an unpolished state.

15:06.071 --> 15:06.906
Okay.

15:07.656 --> 15:10.492
If you ever see Judy again,
you tell me, okay?

15:10.951 --> 15:12.578
You tell me immediately.

15:12.995 --> 15:14.538
I... I hope I see her again.

15:15.122 --> 15:16.957
-I miss her.
-I know.

15:17.750 --> 15:19.752
-I know you loved her.
-You love her too.

15:19.835 --> 15:21.337
We can make other friends.

15:22.004 --> 15:22.838
Right?

15:24.673 --> 15:25.549
Good night.

15:27.885 --> 15:28.844
Good night.

16:05.506 --> 16:07.925
-[Karen] So glad we're doing this.
-Me too.

16:13.472 --> 16:16.558
Funny, we've been neighbors eight years,
and I've never been over.

16:16.642 --> 16:19.520
Oh! That's... Yeah, that's funny.

16:23.607 --> 16:24.858
It's a lovely backyard.

16:25.776 --> 16:26.610
[Jen] Oh.

16:26.902 --> 16:29.029
You really went for it
with the security back here.

16:29.113 --> 16:33.075
Yeah. Well, thanks.
You can never be too safe, right?

16:33.409 --> 16:34.243
Right.

16:35.703 --> 16:39.623
Did your ADT package come with the
Remote Arm/Disarm Via Mobile App?

16:40.040 --> 16:41.166
Yeah.

16:42.376 --> 16:44.962
-Why do you know...
-I'm kind of a home safety nerd.

16:45.462 --> 16:47.131
-[laughs]
-Cool.

16:47.631 --> 16:48.841
Cool-cool, cool-cool.

16:49.258 --> 16:50.300
Where do you keep your gun?

16:51.468 --> 16:53.262
Oh, I... I don't...

16:54.179 --> 16:57.141
Yeah, I'm not, like,
not really a gun person.

16:57.975 --> 16:59.101
-I get it.
-Mm-hm.

16:59.184 --> 17:00.853
I didn't think I was either. [laughs]

17:01.770 --> 17:06.275
But then Jeff got me this adorable pistol
for Christmas and, honestly,

17:06.734 --> 17:08.027
call me a convert.

17:09.028 --> 17:09.862
Okay.

17:10.821 --> 17:11.697
Fun fact.

17:12.031 --> 17:14.533
Did you know if you ask someone
to leave your home and they don't,

17:14.616 --> 17:15.743
you can totally shoot them?

17:16.410 --> 17:17.995
-No, that can't be true.
-It is.

17:18.871 --> 17:19.913
-Fun.
-Mm-hm!

17:23.208 --> 17:24.585
-Okay.
-Okay.

17:25.836 --> 17:27.629
Do you want any more wine?

17:27.713 --> 17:29.548
I should probably get myself home.

17:29.631 --> 17:32.384
If I drink too much,
I break out in full body hives.

17:33.343 --> 17:35.554
-[clears throat]
-Actually, wait.

17:35.637 --> 17:36.472
Um...

17:41.852 --> 17:44.354
Would you mind showing me how to use this?

17:45.898 --> 17:46.732
Uh...

17:48.567 --> 17:50.402
-[gun clicks]
-I'm assuming you do that.

17:53.405 --> 17:55.199
-[beeping]
-[alarm] <i>Armed, stay.</i>

18:35.531 --> 18:37.491
-[banging]
-[alarm beeps]

18:39.952 --> 18:40.786
Shit!

18:41.703 --> 18:42.955
What's going on?

18:43.038 --> 18:45.874
It's okay, honey. Just stay in your room.
Just lock the door.

18:45.958 --> 18:47.251
-Lock the door.
-What?

18:48.627 --> 18:50.629
[beeping continues]

18:50.712 --> 18:52.714
[heartbeat]

19:07.813 --> 19:08.689
Charlie!

19:09.148 --> 19:11.316
-[Charlie] Mom, open the damn door!
-[knocking]

19:14.111 --> 19:16.071
Charlie, you scared the shit out of me!

19:16.155 --> 19:18.115
You scared me.
Those lights are fucking aggressive.

19:18.198 --> 19:19.992
Okay. Hold on. Let me turn this thing off.

19:22.494 --> 19:24.538
-[beeping stops]
-[alarm] <i>Disarmed, ready to arm.</i>

19:25.873 --> 19:27.374
Hey, you're home.

19:28.000 --> 19:32.129
Yeah. Grandma kept calling me Teddy
and touching my face.

19:32.671 --> 19:33.922
Well, that's disturbing.

19:34.256 --> 19:35.174
Yeah.

19:37.593 --> 19:39.469
She has a pill problem.

19:39.928 --> 19:40.762
Mmm.

19:44.266 --> 19:45.225
Hand them over.

19:46.768 --> 19:49.521
-I... I wasn't gonna sell them.
-Mm-hm.

19:50.522 --> 19:52.399
I was saving her from herself.

19:53.066 --> 19:54.026
Really?

19:55.485 --> 19:56.486
Really.

19:56.945 --> 19:57.821
Okay.

19:59.198 --> 20:00.407
I'm glad you're home.

20:04.411 --> 20:05.329
Honey, I'm...

20:06.246 --> 20:08.749
I'm so sorry
that I've been such a shit mom.

20:09.833 --> 20:11.251
-It's all right.
-No.

20:12.252 --> 20:13.420
No, it's not all right.

20:14.963 --> 20:19.509
I'm sorry that I...
that I get so angry sometimes.

20:21.929 --> 20:25.891
And that you saw your dad and me fight,
especially that night.

20:26.391 --> 20:27.267
Okay.

20:27.643 --> 20:30.687
No, really.
I need you to forgive me, Charlie.

20:32.022 --> 20:33.941
I want a clean slate with you.

20:35.359 --> 20:37.069
Just don't be an asshole anymore.

20:38.362 --> 20:40.864
Well, that's, you know, kind of a big ask.

20:42.324 --> 20:43.533
Come here, baby.

20:44.618 --> 20:46.870
Mmm! Oh, God, I love you.

20:46.954 --> 20:48.080
I love you too.

20:48.247 --> 20:49.122
What?

20:50.332 --> 20:52.251
What are those words I just heard?

20:52.334 --> 20:54.211
You didn't say, "Fuck you too"?

20:54.753 --> 20:56.380
-Yeah.
-You said, "I love you too"?

20:56.463 --> 20:57.839
-No.
-[both gasp]

20:59.299 --> 21:00.467
Best day ever.

21:01.218 --> 21:02.094
Best day ever.

21:02.177 --> 21:03.011
[Charlie] Okay.

21:03.095 --> 21:04.638
No. I just need a little more.

21:05.222 --> 21:06.265
Come on, now.

21:19.403 --> 21:21.571
[Jen sighs]
Better put this fucking gun away.

22:03.363 --> 22:04.281
Oh, my God.

22:08.368 --> 22:09.286
[clatter]

22:10.495 --> 22:11.413
Judy?

22:12.039 --> 22:13.040
[Steve] Judy?

22:14.291 --> 22:16.710
Where's Judy?
I need to speak to her immediately.

22:16.793 --> 22:17.961
Well, she's not here.

22:18.045 --> 22:19.463
-Where is she?
-I don't know.

22:21.381 --> 22:23.592
You could've told me that
you're pulling that offer.

22:23.675 --> 22:25.135
It really did fuck me, you know that?

22:25.218 --> 22:26.678
Yeah, well, Judy fucked me.

22:27.471 --> 22:30.766
-There you go. She ruined my life.
-Well, you're not alone.

22:31.391 --> 22:32.476
[Steve sighs]

22:34.353 --> 22:37.230
I told you. Anywhere Judy goes,
chaos follows.

22:38.023 --> 22:38.857
Yup.

22:39.858 --> 22:41.151
-You did.
-[Steve sighs]

22:41.777 --> 22:42.819
[Jen sighs]

22:43.028 --> 22:44.905
I was just trying to look out for you.

22:47.240 --> 22:50.077
Do you want a drink or something?
I can get you a glass.

22:52.287 --> 22:53.455
I don't need a glass.

22:59.544 --> 23:00.587
[Steve sighs]

23:02.964 --> 23:05.759
[chuckles ruefully]
She destroyed me, Jen.

23:06.385 --> 23:09.054
My whole life, my family,
everything I worked for,

23:09.596 --> 23:10.931
it's all gonna disappear.

23:11.473 --> 23:12.391
What happened?

23:13.558 --> 23:14.935
I can't really get into it.

23:16.186 --> 23:18.897
What? She run someone else over?

23:22.234 --> 23:23.360
She told you?

23:27.489 --> 23:28.407
Yeah.

23:31.743 --> 23:32.702
Shit.

23:43.797 --> 23:45.924
Would it make any difference if I...

23:47.884 --> 23:49.428
if I told you I'm sorry?

23:52.139 --> 23:53.807
Not that I was the one driving.

23:58.186 --> 23:59.354
You were in the car?

24:06.820 --> 24:07.779
Jen, that was...

24:09.406 --> 24:12.033
honestly one of the worst moments
of my entire life.

24:13.076 --> 24:14.077
I'm so sorry.

24:14.161 --> 24:15.120
Thank you.

24:16.413 --> 24:17.247
It...

24:18.874 --> 24:20.584
It just killed me not to tell you,

24:21.293 --> 24:22.586
especially once...

24:24.880 --> 24:26.590
I don't know, once I got to know you.

24:31.761 --> 24:33.889
You know, in so many ways,
I feel like we are...

24:35.432 --> 24:36.683
we are in this together.

24:37.350 --> 24:38.977
-You know?
-Are we?

24:39.060 --> 24:39.936
Yeah.

24:41.897 --> 24:43.482
That's why I need you to help me.

24:43.565 --> 24:44.900
I gotta find Judy.

24:45.692 --> 24:46.902
Can you help me do that?

24:48.028 --> 24:49.237
Why didn't you stop?

24:50.113 --> 24:50.947
What?

24:51.323 --> 24:52.324
That night.

24:54.993 --> 24:55.869
Oh.

24:57.746 --> 24:59.039
I mean, I wanted to.

24:59.122 --> 25:01.208
Judy said she wanted to go back,
but she couldn't.

25:04.377 --> 25:05.295
Why not?

25:08.089 --> 25:09.216
I don't... I don't know.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.635
I don't know. She just didn't.

25:12.469 --> 25:13.386
And you didn't.

25:14.471 --> 25:16.515
-Don't do that.
-Do what?

25:17.766 --> 25:20.477
Don't turn this into some
"blame the man" thing.

25:20.560 --> 25:21.811
That's bullshit. Don't.

25:22.604 --> 25:24.397
We both know what Judy is capable of.

25:24.481 --> 25:26.149
Yeah. And I know what you're capable of.

25:27.234 --> 25:28.777
Oh, you have no fucking idea.

25:30.695 --> 25:33.532
Hey, her hand was on the wheel.
Her foot was on the gas.

25:33.615 --> 25:35.116
So don't fucking look at me like that.

25:35.200 --> 25:36.076
Fuck you.

25:36.159 --> 25:38.870
Fuck <i>you!</i>
